	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65030017"><p>Part of the problem is competition.</p><p>Paradoxically, the individual mandate under the ACA creates a situation where you don't actually need to deliver better service to get customers.  For those who correctly point out that the ACA individual mandate was removed as of 2019 ( <a href="https://www.healthinsurance.org/faqs/does-the-presidents-executive-order-mean-the-irs-wont-enforce-the-individual-mandate-penalty/" title="healthinsurance.org">https://www.healthinsurance.or...<span class="substr"> </span></a> [healthinsurance.org] ), there are those of us in states that enacted their own mandates who are subject to similar provisions (minimum $900 or 2.5% of your yearly income penalty in California.  Good luck if you just become une</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65030017">

</div>
